I checked through all the solutions here and observed these trends:
- A lot of solutions use `long`, which violated the requirements of this problem
- Bit shift makes the code less readable

 This solution is similar to Approach 4 in this [solution](https://leetcode.com/problems/divide-two-integers/solution/). But instead of bit shifting, I am using plus and minus operations only. Below are the steps:
- First, we check for the special case `dividend == Integer.MIN_VALUE && divisor == -1`
- We get the absolute value of dividend and divisor
- Do the division for 2 positive numbers using "Adding Powers Of Two" technique

A note on the check `dividend - divisor >= 0` instead of `divisor <= dividend` is to handle the corner case where original `dividend = Integer.MIN_VALUE` and `absDividend = Integer.MIN_VALUE`. 
```java
class Solution {
    public int divide(int dividend, int divisor) {
        if (dividend == Integer.MIN_VALUE && divisor == -1) return Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        int absDividend = getAbs(dividend);
        int absDivisor = getAbs(divisor);
        int res = dividePositive(absDividend, absDivisor);
        return (dividend > 0) == (divisor > 0) ? res : -res;
    }

    int getAbs(int num) {
        return num < 0 ? -num : num;
    }

    int dividePositive(int dividend, int divisor) {
        int count = 0;

        while (dividend - divisor >= 0) {
            int cur = divisor;
            int steps = 1; 
            while (dividend - (cur + cur) > 0) {
                cur = cur + cur;
                steps += steps;
            }
            count += steps;
            dividend = dividend - cur;
        }


        return count;
    }
}
```

