# Approach
The problem can be solved using a recursive approach. We can traverse the binary tree using a pre-order traversal and concatenate the node values into a string. When we reach a leaf node, we can add the string as an integer to our running sum. We repeat this process for each root-to-leaf path in the tree.

# Complexity
- *Time complexity:*
O(n), where n is the number of nodes in the binary tree. We visit each node once.

- *Space complexity:*
 O(h), where h is the height of the binary tree. This is the maximum depth of our recursive stack. In the worst case, where the tree is a linked list, the space complexity is O(n).

