solutions.content:
**Problem statement at a glance:** Given, a tree. We need to find the sum of all root to leaf paths.
**Approach:**
1) We need to go from root to leaf, and whenever we are at leaf, form a number and add it to your result.
2) This can be done with DFS Traversal. Because in DFS we traverse child nodes and we go deep.
**Pictorial Representation:**
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/4e9a516b-e912-4e64-8094-851adbab83f1_1635917131.9978747.png)

**Time Complexity:** As we are traversing each node once, the time complexity will be O(N), where N is number of nodes.
**Space Complexity:** It takes stack space, as we are doing recursion. So space complexity is O(H), where H is the height of tree.
**Code:**
```

class Solution {
    // A helper function to perform DFS
    public int sumNumbersHelper(TreeNode root,int sum)
    {
        // Base case: If the root is null, then it doesnt have any value. So sum is 0
        if(root==null)
        {
            return 0; 
        }
        // If tree has only one node, then the sum is value itself
        if(root.left==null && root.right==null)
        {
            int temp=sum*10+root.val;
            return temp;
        }
        // Else we take the previous sum and move it to left by one digit and root.val should be on unit digit. This can be done as sum*10+root.val
        int temp=sum*10+root.val;
        // Call the left subtree and right subtree and return the sum of them.
        return sumNumbersHelper(root.left,temp)+sumNumbersHelper(root.right,temp);
     }
    public int sumNumbers(TreeNode root) {
      // Calling helper function to perform DFS
      return sumNumbersHelper(root,0);
    }
}
```
